Anne McElvoy interviews Cass Sunstein, a former advisor to Barack Obama and co-author of "Nudge",  a theory of how people can be subliminally prompted to make wiser choices. They discuss how far the state should intervene in our personal freedom and why left-wing Democrats might be their own worst enemy. Runtime 23 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn